This paper deals with the problem of learning the set of pure strategy Nash equilibria in a continuous-action graphical game with quadratic payoffs. This problem falls under the domain of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves regularization techniques (cs.AI) and has a sample complexity analysis (cs.DS) and computational complexity analysis (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.GT and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
